<HEADLINE>
FROM RUSSIA WITH LOTSA LOVE
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By TOM HOFFARTH  
 c.2000 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ The most dangerous mission that the Kings will
have to face in their first-round Stanley Cup playoff series
against the Detroit Red Wings: How to defuse Sergei Federov.
</P>
<P>
   Maybe no one else creates scoring opportunities as he can. After
all, dude's back in the Anna Kournikova sweepstakes, right?
</P>
<P>
   Go back a few weeks ago, when Red Wings coach Scotty Bowman
noticed how despondent his All-Star center was after news leaked
that his dear, sweet Anna had reached verbal agreement to a wedding
with Florida Panthers star Pavel Bure.
</P>
<P>
   Bowman allowed Federov to borrow the team charter and fly to
Phoenix to hook up with her when she was playing at a WTA event in
Scottsdale, Ariz.
</P>
<P>
   The Fedster showed up with an armful of roses.
</P>
<P>
   Now, last week, Bure tells a Russian newspaper that a wedding
ain't happening because ``today I love hockey more than anything
else.'' (This from a guy with a brother named Valeri). Kournikova
also writes on her Web site that ``I never said I was engaged or
planning to get married.... It is hard for me to understand that
some people believe everything they see in the media.''
</P>
<P>
   (Which means... we (begin ital)shouldn't(end ital) believe that
Russian newspaper?)
</P>
<P>
   Did Serge surge ahead? What caused Pavel to repel? Which one of
'em is gonna end up like Dustin Hoffman in ``The Graduate''
pounding on the church glass?
</P>
<P>
   When Anna submits to a live Web chat today (4 p.m., via
www.kournikova.com), our plan is to exacerbate the situation. For
the Kings' sake, of course.
</P>
<P>
   But if they don't make it past the first round, and if somehow
we see a Red Wings-Panthers final series, there should be more than
just Lord Stanley's loving cup at stake.
</P>
<P>
   There'll be more subplots than a you-know-what...
</P>
<P>
   -Hey, priority numbers are already being divvied up for Avengers
playoff tickets, so stop your freakin' shovin'....
</P>
<P>
   -The next time Todd Marinovich's path could cross with Tommy
Maddox's: If the Avengers face the New Jersey Red Dogs in ArenaBowl
XIV this August....
</P>
<P>
   -It was CBS' Ken Venturi who said on the telecast that David
Duval was lining up a shot during the final round of the Masters
that was ``like putting on a marble staircase.''
</P>
<P>
   That's because the greens were as fast as bikini wax, y'know....
</P>
<P>
   -Oh, sorry, double-D. Didn't mean to (begin ital)irritate(end
ital) you....
</P>
<P>
   -So (begin ital)thhhhhis(end ital) is what horse smack sounds
like?
</P>
<P>
   Jenine Sahadi has every right to liken Bob Baffert to a horse's
rear end now, but since The Deputy is the new sheriff in town, the
message has already been delivered....
</P>
<P>
   -That really was the Czech Republic national anthem. It was just
a Howie Mandel rendition....
</P>
<P>
   -Obscure TV stat of the weekend: The Mets' Matt Franco (Westlake
High) set a major-league record last season by drawing 20 walks as
a pinch hitter....
</P>
<P>
   -The Dodgers' scouting report on 6-year-old Cuban refugee Elian
Gonzalez: Plays well with others....
</P>
<P>
   -No one has been allowed to start selling off souvenir chunks of
the Kingdome yet because they're going to pile it all up outside
Safeco Field and try to prevent ARod from leaving....
</P>
<P>
   -One last thought on the just-concluded ``Real World/Road Rule
Challenge'': great clothesline Amaya put on Veronica during the
flag football game. But then watching that whiny chick injure
herself during (begin ital)every single event(end ital) was an even
better payoff.
</P>
</TEXT>
