NEW YORK TIMES CORRECTIONS FOR MONDAY, April 10 
Eds.: These corrections will appear in The New York Times on
Monday. Days and dates refer to the original article's transmission
by the New York Times News Service, and may need to be adjusted by
NYT clients.)  
(ss) 
 c.2000 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   BC-RUSSIA-CHECHNYA-NYT (moved Wednesday, April 5)
</P>
<P>
   An article sent on Wednesday, April 5 about a Russian town's
concerns over the war in Chechnya misstated the age of Oleg
Malyavkin, a disabled Russian Army veteran who commented on the war
and who took part in the invasion of Czechoslovakia in 1968. He is
54, not 44.
</P>
</TEXT>
