that causes AIDS. The disease has devastated the skating world in
the last decade, most notably taking the life of John Curry, the
1976 Olympic champion. Galindo, decided to speak about HIV because
the truth has always been liberating for him, especially in a sport
where rumor and gossip often take on the force of fact. ``Being
openly gay, having the cards laid on the table, made everything
easier for me in skating and making my choices in whatever road I
took in life,'' he says. (Tim Shaffer/The New York Times)
