RAMPAGE-KILLERS-II -- Jeffrey Wade Wallace, 38, incarcerated in the
Hardee Correctional Institution in Bowling Green, Fla. Wallace,
like other rampage killers, was convinced he was defending himself
against an intricate conspiracy. To this day, Wallace, insists that
he had no choice but to open fire in 1997 at a Key West bar where
he once worked, killing one person and injuring three others.
Wallace's lawyers argued unsuccessfully that he was insane, but
Wallace insists his actions were perfectly rational. ``I was trying
to save myself and my family,'' says Wallace. (Fred R. Conrad/The
New York Times)
</P>
